{% import "macros/paths" as paths %}
Prefer the Edit tool for targeted changes in known files:

    Read {{ paths.sym("<file>", "process", ext) }} ← Read first
    Edit {{ paths.sym("<file>", "process", ext) }} ← old_string/new_string - remember that the path must be identical to the prior read

All writes to `@/` paths are tree-sitter validated and safe. Invalid syntax returns an error, not a broken file.
